@namespace DotNetCloud.Modules.Notes.UI

@*
    Help content for the Notes module.
    Based on docs/user/NOTES.md.
*@

<div class="help-content">
    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Overview</h2>
        <p>DotNetCloud Notes is a Markdown-first note-taking system with folders, tags, version history, cross-module links, and sharing. Create, edit, and organize your notes with rich formatting.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Creating Notes</h2>
        <ol class="help-steps">
            <li>Open <strong>Notes</strong> from the left sidebar.</li>
            <li>Click <strong>New Note</strong>.</li>
            <li>Enter a <strong>Title</strong> (required).</li>
            <li>Write your content in Markdown or plain text.</li>
            <li>Optionally select a <strong>Folder</strong>, add <strong>Tags</strong>, or toggle <strong>Pin</strong> or <strong>Favorite</strong>.</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Save</strong>.</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Editing Notes</h2>
        <p>Click on a note to open it. Edit the title or content, then click <strong>Save</strong>. Each save creates a new version in the note's history.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Markdown Support</h2>
        <p>Notes support full Markdown formatting:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Bold:</strong> <code>**text**</code></li>
            <li><em>Italic:</em> <code>*text*</code></li>
            <li>Headings: <code># H1</code> through <code>###### H6</code></li>
            <li>Lists: <code>- item</code> or <code>1. item</code></li>
            <li>Task lists: <code>- [ ] todo</code> or <code>- [x] done</code></li>
            <li>Code blocks with triple backticks, links, images, tables, blockquotes, and more</li>
            <li>Emoji shortcodes: <code>:smile:</code>, <code>:rocket:</code></li>
        </ul>
        <p>The editor provides a split-pane interface with toolbar, edit mode, split mode, and preview mode.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Folders</h2>
        <p>Folders provide hierarchical organization. Create folders in the sidebar, nest them under parent folders, and optionally set a color. Drag notes between folders to reorganize.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Tags</h2>
        <p>Add tags to notes for cross-folder categorization. Click a tag in the sidebar to filter notes by that tag.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Version History</h2>
        <p>Each save creates a version. Open a note's version history to view, compare, or restore previous versions.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Tips &amp; Tricks</h2>
        <ul class="help-tips">
            <li>Use folders for broad categories and tags for cross-cutting topics.</li>
            <li>Pin frequently accessed notes to the top of your list.</li>
            <li>Use the search bar to quickly find notes by title or content.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
</div>
